Outcome: create a program that will automatically create a notes folder and connect that folder to github.

inputs:
    * notes folder name
    * note folder location (default home)
    * github account

requirements:
    * Vim
    * Github account
    * Bash command line
    * Linux
==========================

1.
    (home folder)
    check if bashrc exists
    add code to bashrc
    check if vimrc exists
    add code to vimrc
    (probably should metnion at somepoint to user that the keywords used in the bashrc file and vimrc file are being used, then handle that in someway)
2. 
    create folder in location
    make a git repo
    link to git account

==========================
Test program on a Linux virtual machine

==========================
put on pip store and/or make open source
